        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "\"Colorizing\" (\"color\" as in \"colored noise\", in which different frequencies may have different magnitudes) transforms a set of uncorrelated random variables into a new set of random variables with the desired covariance. When a coloring transform is applied to a sample of points distributed according to a multivariate normal distribution with identity covariance and zero mean, the covariance of the transformed sample is approximately the covariance matrix used in the coloring transform."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
